deck: Frank Boles was a corrections officer at Arkham Asylum. Boles was in league with the Joker for quite some time until his usefulness ran out.
description:
Officer Frank Boles was a corrections officer at Arkham Asylum. Officer Boles eventually joined Joker's inner circle. Boles would often assist Joker with his escape attempts in exchange for favors. Boles was well aware of the Joker holding Jason Todd prisoner in an abandoned wing of Arkham Asylum but nothing more ever came of it.

Later on, Joker informs Boles that he has devised a plan to entrap the Batman at Arkham Asylum. After being captured by the Batman and reprocessed at Arkham Asylum, the Joker sprang his trap with the help of Harley Quinn. When Batman chased after the Joker, he noticed a security feed that showed Boles knocking Commissioner Gordon unconscious.

Batman gives up the chase and makes his way to the processing center where he left Gordon. Batman finds Boles' flask and tracks the unique scent in order to locate Boles. Joker eventually realizes that the Batman is no longer playing his little game because he is too busy tracking down Boles in order to get to Gordon.

Joker gives Harley the order to kill Boles and dress him up as a means to antagonize the Batman. When Batman finds Boles, he discovers his body has been tied to a gurney in a vertical position. Boles' face is done up to look like the Joker with a big sign tied to his chest saying "Ha Ha Ha"
name: Frank Boles

deck: Martin Reyna is a S.H.I.E.L.D. agent in charge of S.T.A.K.E. He has the ability to transform into a Werewolf.
description:
Origin

Martin Reyna is a SHIELD agent whom was in charge of the organization's special S.T.A.K.E. unit. He has the power to change into a werewolf-like creature. How he came into this possition and his background has not yet been revealed.

Creation

Martin Reyna was created by AL Ewing and Stefano Caselli and first appeared in S.H.I.E.L.D. Vol.3 issue 9 (2015). He then became one of the stars of the new Howling Commandos series. He should not be mistaken for the other Warwolf (Vic Marcus) character that was part of the previous monster-team.

Major Story Arcs

A new Warwolf

Martin has taken the alias of Warwolf, much like the previous werewolf-like agent Warwolf (Vic Marcus). He has been working Paul Kraye on a number of top-secret projects. When SHIELD agent Dum Dum Dugan was brought back from the dead, he was added to the rooster, much to the dislike of Martin. He and Paul Kraye eventually agreed to try to get rid of Dugan in fear of him discovering their secret projects.

description: Shock & Awe are conjoined twins working for Anthem. Their listing in Anthem's database includes "Aural detonation" (of a considerable nature) and "Physical limitations" (presumably their conjoined status.) As part of Anthem's Los Angeles Strike Force, they helped take the Midnighter prisoner but were later killed during his escape.
name: Shock & Awe

description:
Rosie is a super-powered woman working for Anthem. Their database describes her powers as "Biological ordinance," although it's not clear what that means. She possesses considerable strength and can either fly or jump extremely high. Her skin and hair are metallic in look and texture.

As part of Anthem's Los Angeles Strike Team, she helped take Midnighter prisoner but was killed in his subsequent escape.
name: Rosie

description:
Spangle is a super-powered man working for Anthem. Their database credits him with a "Psionic distortion field," which disorients opponents. He is also listed as having "Pharmacutical limitations, although what kind are not specified.

As part of Anthem's Los Angeles Strike Team, he helped capture Midnighter. However, he was either killed or grievously wounded in the attempt and subsequently replaced.
name: Spangle

description:
Dawn is a super-powered woman who works for Anthem. Their database describes her as a "Biological solar battery" which powers her flight and heat blasts from her eyes and hands. The entry also mentions "Meteorlogical limitations" which may indicate a need to recharge, although she also appears vulnerable to electricity. She has gone toe-to-toe with Midnighter and held her own until stunned by her own guards.

As part of Anthem's Los Angeles Strike Force, she helped capture Midnighter but was subsequently killed in his escape.
name: Dawn

deck: Ryuu is a high level dungeon explorer. Her familia was killed in a trap set by another familia. She was the only one to survive the trap.
description:
Origin

Ryuu was known as the Tempest in the Astraea familia. The Astraea familia, including Ryuu, got caught in a trap set by a rival familia. All of her familia members were killed except for her. She, later, tracked down the rival familia and killed every single member. She was, later, found, near death, in an alley by Syr and Mama Mia, who took her in and now she is a waitress for Mama Mia.

Appearance

Ryuu is a female elf who is usually seen wearing a maid outfit in the restaurant as she works for Mama Mia. She has blue eyes and green hair with a thin and nimble body stature.

She has also been shown wearing dungeon gear. The dungeon gear she wears is a green hood shaped like a leaf, a white shirt with no sleeves and buckles and straps placed throughout the outfit.
name: Ryuu Lyon
